Mira R. Ricardel has been appointed as Assistant to the President and Deputy National Security Advisor by President Donald J. Trump's National Security Advisor, Ambassador John Bolton. Ricardel brings over two decades of national security policy and program experience, as well as more than a decade of private-sector experience in aerospace. She has worked in the Departments of State, Defense, and Commerce, and also in the U.S. Senate office of Republican Leader Bob Dole. Ricardel's expertise includes national security matters related to alliances, defense posture, technology security, foreign security assistance, and arms control. She has previously held positions such as Under Secretary of Commerce for Export Administration, Acting Assistant Secretary of Defense for International Security Policy, and Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for Eurasia. Ricardel played a significant role in garnering support for United States and coalition operations in Afghanistan after the September 11, 2001 attacks. She holds a B.S. magna cum laude in Foreign Services from Georgetown University and has completed doctoral coursework at The Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy at Tufts University.